The paper deals with the problem of navigating in 3D virtual environments using touch devices, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed solution involves using reinforcement learning (RL) to learn a new interaction protocol, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions computer assisted design (CAD) models and geographical information systems (GIS), which are examples of graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications, respectively. Finally, the paper uses a variational auto encoder (VAE) for state representation learning, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG).
